<p>To register your child 17 years of age or younger for ImmTrac participation, documentation of parental consent is required. Consent is only required one time and is valid until your child turns 18. For persons 18 years of age and older, an adult registration form is required for participation.</p>
<ol>
	<li>Download the appropriate registration form on the <a title="ImmTrac Publications page" href="/immunize/immtrac/forms.shtm#Registration">ImmTrac Publications page<br/><br/></a>
		<ul>
			<li>For Adults - Download an "ImmTrac Adult Registration Form" (EF11-13366)</li>
			<li>For Children - Download an "ImmTrac Child Registration Form" (C-7)</li>
		</ul>
		<p><br/><em>NOTE: You must use a separate form for each individual.</em></p>
	</li>
	
	<li>Complete the form, print and sign it.<br/><br/></li>
	<li>Submit the completed form to DSHS by one of the following methods:<br/><br/>
		<ul>
			<li>
				Send to DSHS via Fax:<br/>
				(512) 776-7790 (Austin)<br/>
				(866) 624-0180 (toll-free)<br/><br/>
			</li>			
			<li>
				Send to DSHS by Mail:<br/>
				Texas Department of State Health Services<br/>
				Immunizations Unit, ImmTrac Group<br/>
				MC 1946, PO Box 149347<br/>
				Austin, TX 78714-9347<br/><br/>
			</li>
			<li>Deliver to your <a title="" href="http://www.dshs.state.tx.us/regions/lhds.shtm">participating local health department</a><br/><br/></li>
			<li>Deliver to any health-care provider that is registered with ImmTrac</li>
		</ul>
	</li>
</ol>



